Reclusa::

She was slightly shocked he knew her name when she had not spoken it,
but did not let it show.  He probably was listening in on the whole
trip through Perceptor's comlink, she thought. She smiled as he shook
her hand. "I am pleased to be here. I must admit, I was rather hoping
that the Maximals would have been stamped out by now. But pleased to
see that they have not been able to stop us either."  She still stood
regally before him. "I will tell you this now. I do have personal
plans of revenge later on. A score to settle with them, if you will.
But revenge is a dish best served cold. So I will wait for the proper
time. But untill that time comes, I wish to assist you in dealing with
this, ah, Unicron situation."  She smiled at him with a sweet, yet
slightly evil look. "If this Unicron wins, then we can't win over the
Maximals. So, let me know how I can help with this matter."

She kept her cool, confident and royal optics on Hydras. If her
progams ever evolved into anything, it was never trust another bot. Never.
